        "parentPluginId": "@kbn/grok-heuristics",
        "id": "def-common.assembleGrokProcessor",
        "type": "Function",
        "tags": [],
        "label": "assembleGrokProcessor",
        "description": [
          "\nOrchestrates the full grok processor assembly pipeline:\n  1. For each pattern group, compute review fields from nodes\n  2. Call the provided reviewFn (LLM review) with those fields\n  3. Assemble a GrokProcessorResult from nodes + review\n  4. Merge all per-group processors into one\n  5. Return a Streamlang GrokProcessor ready for simulation/use\n\nCallers supply their own reviewFn to handle LLM transport\n(streaming API, in-process call, kbnClient.request, etc.).\n\nMessages passed to reviewFn are truncated to avoid polluting\nthe LLM context. Groups are processed in parallel via\nPromise.allSettled; individual failures are silently dropped\nso partial results still produce a merged processor."
        ],
        "signature": [
          "({ from, patternGroups, reviewFn, }: ",
          {
            "pluginId": "@kbn/grok-heuristics",
            "scope": "common",
            "docId": "kibKbnGrokHeuristicsPluginApi",
